SkemaBase Project Instructions

Description:
- Define database schemas using plain English.
- Generate JSON IR, SQL DDL (PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite), ORM migrations, and ER diagrams.

Syntax:
  <Entity> has attributes: <name>[:<type>] [unique] [not null] [default <expr>], …
  <Entity> has many <Target>
  <Entity> has one <Target>
  <Entity> belongs to <Target>
  <Entity> has and belongs to many <Target>

BNF Grammar:
```
<Schema>       ::= <Statement>*
<Statement>    ::= <EntityDecl> | <AttrDecl> | <RelDecl>
<EntityDecl>   ::= <Identifier>
<AttrDecl>     ::= <Identifier> "has attributes:" <AttrList>
<AttrList>     ::= <Attr> ("," <Attr>)*
<Attr>         ::= <Name> [":" <Type>] ["unique"] ["not null"] ["default" <Expr>]
<RelDecl>      ::= <Identifier> <RelType> <IdentifierList>
<RelType>      ::= "has many" | "has one" | "belongs to" | "has and belongs to many"
<IdentifierList> ::= <Identifier> ("," <Identifier>)*
```

Project Structure:
- examples/     Sample schemas (.sb), IR (.ir.json), and SQL (.sql).
- skemabase-js/ JavaScript SDK
  - src/tokenizer.js   Lexical analysis
  - src/parser.js      AST generation
  - src/astToIR.js     IR conversion
  - tests/             Unit tests (Jest)
- todo.md        Phase-by-phase roadmap
- README.md      Usage, quickstart, and developer docs

Development Commands:
- cd skemabase-js && npm install && npm test   Run SDK tests
- skemabase parse <file.sb> --output <file.json>
- skemabase generate sql <file.sb> --dialect postgresql --output <file.sql>

Coding Guidelines:
- Fix issues at the root cause; avoid quick patches.
- Keep changes minimal and focused on the user’s request.
- Update documentation (README.md, todo.md) as needed.
- Use `apply_patch` for file edits and ensure pre-commit checks pass.
- Run existing tests; add new tests for new functionality.

Roadmap Phases (see todo.md):
- Phase 1: Testing & CI/CD (complete)
- Phase 2: Core Parsing & IR (complete)
- Phase 3: SQL Generation (MVP)
  - Design mapping IR → SQL DDL constructs
  - Implement SQL generator for PostgreSQL (red–green development)
  - Add support for SQLite
  - Create SQL generator tests (IR → SQL → IR)
  - Integrate `generate sql` command in CLI and expose `generateSQL` in the SDK
- Phase 4: Relationships & Constraints
- Phase 5+: ORM templates, CLI polish, diagram generation, documentation